About the Job:

The Analytics Engineer has a deep understanding of business needs while applying software engineering best practices to implement data pipelines and create data abstractions that help the company to make better decisions faster.

The analytics engineering workflow is to clean, transform, and model raw data into consumable information for strategic decision-making. During the process of obtaining the raw data until the availability of the cleaned and transformed data, the analytics engineer tests the data to guarantee the quality, documents the business rules and creates models to ensure that they are executed in a scalable and reliable way in a production environment.

This role has more engineering skills than your average analyst and is more curious to answer analytical business questions than the average of data engineers. Because of that, the analytics engineering team works closely with our business and tech teams to build a better understanding of the usage of data and how our tools positively affect teams at QuintoAndar.




